    "updated_at": "2015-09-16T03:45:02Z",
    "body": "[setMenu()](http://electron.atom.io/docs/v0.32.0/api/browser-window/#win-setmenu-menu-os-x) seems to be applicable on `OS X` only, per documentation.\n\nI did anyways try it on `Linux`, it worked, but then the entire menu was gone. I guess i need to define required menu items, and then, set the menu bar accordingly.\n\nOn a side note, with the same code on `OS X`, I can't make the window fullscreen using the keyboard shortcut `Ctrl-Cmd-F`, as expected.\n\n``` javascript\nmainWindow = new BrowserWindow({\n     width: 480,\n     height: 640,\n     resizable: false,\n     fullscreen: false,\n});\n```\n\nHowever, on Linux/Windows, it behaves differently.\n\nLooks like there is some inconsistent behavior with respect to setting `fullscreen` option to `false`.\n"
  },
