    "created_at": "2015-09-16T08:56:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-16T08:56:15Z",
    "body": "`mainWindow.setMenu()` shouldn't be `OS X` only AFAIK. I think that's a typo due to confusion with  [`app.dock.setMenu()`](http://electron.atom.io/docs/v0.32.0/api/app/) (someone correct me if I'm wrong?).\n\nRight, the entire menu was gone. Sorry if I wasn't clear enough -- there's a menu item with a keyboard command bound to it by default. So, removing the menu removes the keyboard command. You're right that you'll want to set up your own menu bar (or remove it if you so desire).\n\nDunno what to tell you about `Ctrl+Cmd+F`. :-\\\n"
  },
