    "created_at": "2015-09-16T16:01:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-16T16:01:56Z",
    "body": "The `fullscreen` option is not a hard limitation, you can still control the fullscreen with APIs. On Linux and Windows the `F11` is bound to call `setFullScreen` API in the default menu, if you don't want to respond to `F11`, you should set a custom menu for your app.\n\nAn example can be found at https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/docs/api/menu.md, what you need to do is to remove the `Toggle Full Screen` item.\n"
  },
